ile-first design, as requested, to create an elegant and professional UI. I\'ve decided the design will fill the screen on mobile devices but center on desktop. The CSS styles will reside inside a `<style>` tag, containing standard animations (fading, slide-ups, bouncing ball emoji \360\237\217\217, shimmering credit text, glowing pulse effect). I\'ll also be using raw inline SVGs for all icons, as this approach is bulletproof, customizable, fast, and meets the requirement for zero external libraries, and ensures offline compatibility.\n\n\n**Implementing the Animations**\n\nI\'m now implementing the animations as I design the UI. I\'ve begun with the confetti, fireworks, and typing dots effects, ensuring they function as described in the specifications. I\'m focusing on the timing, color randomization, and integration with user interactions. Next, I\'ll incorporate the gate pulse, button press, and splash exit animations to give the app a polished feel. I\'ll make sure each style is efficient and meets the goals.\n\n\n"
