  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Verifying the Linter**\n\nOkay, so I confirmed the linter isn\'t set up yet. No \"lint\" script in `package.json` \342\200\223 that explains the error. It\'s all working as expected. Now I\'m checking the other scripts present in `package.json`.\n\n\n**Confirming Implementations Complete**\n\nI\'ve verified the `package.json` file once more, and, as expected, it does not include a \"lint\" script. The build succeeded without any issues, which is a good sign. Moving on to `index.html`, I\'m confirming all splash screen elements are present and correctly implemented, the fade and app transitions are all there, and the tab switching with the fade and slide functions as expected. I\'m satisfied all requirements are met!\n\n\n**Validating Fan Mode**\n\nI can confirm that the \"MatchMood AI\" title is present, with the required styling. The tab-dependent subtitle is also correctly implemented. Help Mode elements are all included as requested, and the system prompt matches exactly. Finally, I\'m validating that the map responds to matching gates. Moving on, I am validating Fan Mode!\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the single-file mobile-first web application for **MatchMood AI**, implementing all specified visual identities, interactive layouts, and generative flows.\n\nHere is a summary of the accomplishments and the design concepts integrated:\n\n### \360\237\214\237 Design Concept & Animations\n* **Deep Night Theme**: Styled with a deep premium background (`#1C1C2E`), clean contrasting slates, and rich golden highlights (`#D4AF37`) for an elite stadium presence.\n* **Animated Splash Screen**: On load, a full-screen entry introduces a large, bouncing cricket ball emoji (`\360\237\217\217`), the \"MatchMood AI\" logo, and the tagline *\"Feel the game. Find your way.\"*, grounded by a shimmering *Powered by Gemini* indicator. Over exactly 2.5 seconds, the splash fades out smoothly to reveal the main app container.\n* **HTML5 Canvas Animations**: Integrated a lightweight game loop running on `<canvas>` at 60 FPS to handle dynamic interactive triggers:\n  * **Wicket Confetti**: Triggers an explosion of 80 multicolored falling particles drifting with realistic gravity variables over 3.5 seconds.\n  * **Explosive Six Fireworks**: Triggers a radial starburst of 12 sparkling rays scaling and fading out from the center tap point.\n* **Typing Indicator**: Features standard 3-dot staggered bouncing indicators colored in Mumbai Indians navy blue.\n* **Transition & Stagger**: Tab switching utilizes 250ms fade and subtle 10px slide-up animations to maintain interface fluidity.\n\n### \360\237\217\237 Section 1: Stadium Navigator (Help Mode)\n* **SVG Wankhede Map**: Contains a complete top-down orthographic representation of Wankhede Stadium, including the central green outfields, pitch alignments, stands, and 4 gates.\n* **Pulsing Gate Intelligence**: When the AI response contains gate mentions (e.g., Gate 1 to Gate 4), the corresponding map gate transforms into a glowing, pulsing green neon indicator, automatically fading scale after 6.5 seconds.\n* **Quick-Tap Navigation shortcuts**: Instantly proxy queries regarding food stalls, restrooms, and seat locators straight to the Gemini 1.5 Flash engine.\n\n### \360\237\217\217 Section 2: Fan Zone (Fan Mode)\n* **Live Score HUD Banner**: Display of live match statuses (`MI 142/4 (16.2 ov)`) featuring a pulsing red recording emblem.\n* **Loud Celebration Reactions**: \"Wicket!\" and \"Six!\" triggers query custom personality prompts, outputting energetic cricket commentary reactions in red/blue cards.\n* **Chant Generator**: Composes dynamic 4-line rhyming chants supporting Mumbai Indians, complete with an interactive clipboard utility with direct visual copy-paste confirmations.\n* **Match Predictions**: Processes specific tactical queries to analyze match momentum and presents humorous predictive win-percentage estimates inside warm golden cards.\n\n### \360\237\224\221 Robust Key Management & Error Handling\n* **API Manager**: Includes a collapsible top drawer for pasting Gemini API Keys. Successfully locks the key, populates persistent `localStorage`, and displays a green verified badge.\n* **High-Tolerance Interceptors**: Includes a custom 8-second query timer. Handlers gracefully capture API timeouts or connection drops and render red indicators encouraging retries.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 231799456
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
